title: Volvo car sales in Sweden 2009 to 2019
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Units sold, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 4 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2017 to 2012.
Likewise, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019 to 2017.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2011 to 2009.
Additionally, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2012 to 2011.
gold: In 2019 , over 65 thousand Volvo cars were sold in Sweden . This was a decrease of more than four thousand vehicles when compared to the previous year , and the second time since 2012 that the company did not experience a rise in sales . Nevertheless , Volvo was actually the leading passenger car brand in Sweden that year , surpassing Volkswagen by more than 16 thousand sold passenger cars .
